.:: Puzzle 4x3-Level-4-13::.
The people have 3 different jobs:  accountant, analyst, fisherman
3 different brands of cigars are smoked: pall-mall, chaman, prince
The people grow 3 different varities of flowers: marigold, daffodil, iris
The people use 3 different means of transport: airplane, motorbike, trike
1. the accountant is on the left or right of the analyst##3
2. the accountant is on the left of the analyst##1
3. the analyst is in an even position##4
4. the prince-smoker is on the far right##1
5. the person who growsmarigold is the person driving the trike##1
6. the chaman-smoker is in the middle##1
7. the person driving the motorbike is on the far left##1
8. the person who growsdaffodil is on the left of the person driving the trike##1
9. the chaman-smoker is on the left of the person who growsiris##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |     2     |     3     |
| Job           | accountant | analyst   | fisherman |
| Cigar   | pall-mall  | chaman    | prince    |
| Flower         | daffodil    | marigold | iris   |
| Transport     | motorbike  | trike     | airplane  |

